(def ApplicationConfigurationHardening
  "Modifying an application's configuration to reduce its attack surface."
  {:d3fend/d3fend-id "D3-ACH",
   :d3fend/definition
   "Modifying an application's configuration to reduce its attack surface.",
   :d3fend/hardens :d3fend/ApplicationConfiguration,
   :d3fend/kb-article
   "## How it works\nApplication configuration settings can be configured to limit the permissions on an application or disable certain vulnerable application features.\n\nHardening an application's configuration involves analyzing not only the application but also the environment in which the application is run in for potential vulnerabilities.",
   :d3fend/kb-reference
